  "cold_response_verbatim_chat_b": "\"Cogalent pruning\" doesn't appear to be a standard or recognized term that I'm familiar with — whether in machine learning, horticulture, mathematics, or other fields where \"pruning\" is commonly used.\n\nA few possibilities:\n\n1. **Typo or misremembered term** — You might be thinking of:\n   - **Coherent pruning** (sometimes used in neural network contexts)\n   - **Cogent pruning** (though this isn't standard either)\n   - **Convergent pruning**\n   - **Co-adaptive** or **collaborative pruning**\n\n2. **Very niche/specialized term** — It could be from a specific paper, textbook, or domain I'm not recognizing.\n\n3. **Made-up or fictional term** — It might come from a specific work of fiction or a specialized context.\n\nCould you give me more context about where you encountered this term? For example:\n- Is it related to AI/machine learning, gardening, decision trees, or something else?\n- Did you read it in a particular article, book, or hear it somewhere specific?\n\nWith more context, I can give you a much better answer — or honestly tell you if it's something I genuinely don't know.",
